_header: Lo here is noted and put in memory
Subjects: chronicles, verse in; Henry V, death of; envoys; elegies
_description: The masses to be sung over the tomb of Henry V, translating Latin list which precedes these verses, and followed by Envoy, in Part VII of Fabyan’s Chronicle, Septima Pars, Henrici Quinti — eight stanzas rhyme royal including 4-stanza Envoy

HarEng766.First Lines:
Loo here is notid And put in memoryThat ouer this Actes noble and
                    marciallThis excellent prynce this fifte kyng henryhis Soule to endowe
                    he was memoriall…
HarEng766.Last Lines:
…Aboue the Serarchies he is I trist now stallidThat was on
                    Erth kyng of kynges called
